Package com.mappedin.sdk

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LocationGenerator
    Location Generator, provide function to MappedIn.getVenue(Venue, boolean, LocationGenerator, MappedinCallback), for generating customize location
    MappedinCallback<Result>
    A interface with function that will be called when webApi call have come back from the network
    MapViewDelegate
    A delegate to handle callbacks from a MapView
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Category
    A Category is a collection of similar Locations, which may have parent or children categories.
    Coordinate
    A Coordinate represents a 3-dimensional position on the Earth's surface.
    Directions
    A Directions object will contain a list of Nodes on a path, and a corresponding list of Instruction objects representing the instructions to display to the user.
    ImageCollection
    A collection of references to images of various sizes.
    Instruction
    An instruction for a user to get from one Node to another.
    Location
    A location is something like a store or washroom on a map.
    Map
    A Map belonging to a given venue.
    MappedIn
    MappedIn class use to connect mappedin server for Venue data.
    MapView
    MapView is a custom view designed to handle displaying Maps for a Venue.
    MapViewCamera
    The MapViewCamera allows you to control the camera on the MapView.
    Navigatable
    All classes that implement the Navigatable protocol can be navigated to and from any other Navigatable object.
    Overlay
    A 2D overlay on MapView.
    Overlay2DImage
    A 2D image overlay on MapView.
    Overlay2DLabel
    A 2D image overlay on MapView.
    Path
    Path to show on a MapView.
    Polygon
    The Polygon class represents the 3D shape of a Loction on a Map.
    RawData
    A wrapper class representing MappedIn JSON data.
    Venue
    A Venue is a specific place (like a mall) with one or more maps (typically representing different floors) and locations (stores, washrooms, elevators, etc).
    Vortex
    A Vortex is a special entity that represents a link between two or more maps at a given venue.
